item.title: No Future in England's Dreaming: 1977 Wrap-Up pt.1
item.description:
We’re almost at the end of our 1977 series, but in true LITM fashion why have just one show on a topic when you could have two? Across this and the next episode we’ll be filling in a few gaps we haven’t touched on so far, and providing some broad economic and political scene-setting for this seminal year in both Britain and the States.
In this episode we hear about the emergent neoliberal order, the oil crisis, austerity then and now, and OPEC... Feed: https://anchor.fm/s/4f5a79dc/podcast/rss

item.title: ROI Framework for Data Teams
item.description: In this episode of the Lights On Data Show, George Firican interviews Ollie Hughes, CEO and co-founder of Count, to explore the challenge every data team faces: showing real Return on Investment (ROI). Ollie shares a clear framework built on four principles that help data teams break free from the 'service trap' and make a measurable business impact... Feed: https://anchor.fm/s/5afa3048/podcast/rss
